


6) If we want Total Sales, And Also the Year and Month of Sale we can use below

A) 
SELECT CONCAT(EXTRACT(YEAR FROM sale_date),'-',EXTRACT(MONTH FROM sale_date)) AS yearmonth, SUM(amount) AS total_sales FROM sales GROUP BY yearmonth;

+-----------+-------------+
| yearmonth | total_sales |
+-----------+-------------+
| 2023-1    |   879637.76 |
| 2023-2    |   748929.85 |
| 2023-3    |   863352.33 |
| 2023-6    |   788915.70 |
| 2023-5    |   854181.71 |
| 2023-4    |   827953.66 |
+-----------+-------------+




OR  [We can Use the Below One as we have Use the YEAR_MONTH Function in that]



B)
SELECT EXTRACT(YEAR_MONTH FROM sale_date) AS yearmonth, SUM(amount) AS total_sales FROM sales GROUP BY yearmonth;

+-----------+-------------+
| yearmonth | total_sales |
+-----------+-------------+
|    202301 |   879637.76 |
|    202302 |   748929.85 |
|    202303 |   863352.33 |
|    202306 |   788915.70 |
|    202305 |   854181.71 |
|    202304 |   827953.66 |
+-----------+-------------+









 DATE_ADD  /  DATE_SUB
======================

7) If we want to Add 10 Days to the Current Date

SELECT date_add(current_date, interval 10 day) AS new_date;

+------------+
| newdate    |
+------------+
| 2026-01-06 |
+------------+







8) If we want to Sub 10 Days to the Current Date


SELECT date_sub(current_date, interval 10 day) AS new_date;

+------------+
| new_date   |
+------------+
| 2025-12-17 |
+------------+










