DATE_FORMAT
==============


10) A) If we Use Capital “Y” It will Give Year in below format

SELECT DATE_FORMAT('1998-03-06', '%Y');

+---------------------------------+
| DATE_FORMAT('1998-03-06', '%Y') |
+---------------------------------+
| 1998                            |
+---------------------------------+




10) B) If we Use Capital “M” It will Give Month in below format

SELECT DATE_FORMAT('1998-03-06', '%M');

+---------------------------------+
| DATE_FORMAT('1998-03-06', '%M') |
+---------------------------------+
| March                           |
+---------------------------------+



10) C) If we Use Capital “D” It will Give Day in below format

SELECT DATE_FORMAT('1998-03-06', '%D');

+---------------------------------+
| DATE_FORMAT('1998-03-06', '%D') |
+---------------------------------+
| 6th                             |
+---------------------------------+












11) A) If we Use Small “y” It will Give Year in below format

SELECT DATE_FORMAT('1998-03-06', '%y');

+---------------------------------+
| DATE_FORMAT('1998-03-06', '%y') |
+---------------------------------+
| 98                              |
+---------------------------------+









11) B) If we Use Small “m” It will Give Month in below format

SELECT DATE_FORMAT('1998-03-06', '%m');

+---------------------------------+
| DATE_FORMAT('1998-03-06', '%m') |
+---------------------------------+
| 03                              |
+---------------------------------+









11) C) If we Use Small “d” It will Give Day in below format

SELECT DATE_FORMAT('1998-03-06', '%d');

+---------------------------------+
| DATE_FORMAT('1998-03-06', '%d') |
+---------------------------------+
| 06                              |
+---------------------------------+












